>>> # Ask the user for the current time
>>> current_time = int(input("Enter the current time (in 24-hour format): \"))
Enter the current time (in 24-hour format): 13
>>> # Ask the user for the number of hours to wait
>>> wait_hours = int(input("Enter the number of hours to wait for the alar\m: "))
Enter the number of hours to wait for the alarm: 50
>>> # Calculate future time
>>> future_time = (current_time + wait_hours) % 24
>>> # Display the result
>>> print(f"The alarm will go off at {future_time}:00 on the 24-hour clock\.")
The alarm will go off at 15:00 on the 24-hour clock.
